# Run the tests

Tests are run with [pytest] via [tox].

## Quick run

To run tests directly with pytest:

```bash
{% if use_uv_lock %}uv run --locked pytest{% else %}pytest{% endif %}
```

## Full tox suite

To run the same suite that CI runs (including lint and type-checking):

```bash
tox -p
```

To run a single environment:

```bash
tox -e py312          # tests only
tox -e lint           # prek hooks
tox -e type-checking  # pyright
tox -e docs           # documentation build
```

## Running a specific test

```bash
{% if use_uv_lock %}uv run --locked pytest tests/test_example.py{% else %}pytest tests/test_example.py{% endif %}
{% if use_uv_lock %}uv run --locked pytest tests/test_example.py::test_add_3_4{% else %}pytest tests/test_example.py::test_add_3_4{% endif %}
```

## Coverage report

The test run generates a coverage report in `reports/`:

```bash
{% if use_uv_lock %}uv run --locked pytest --cov={{ package_name }} --cov-report=html{% else %}pytest --cov={{ package_name }} --cov-report=html{% endif %}
```

[pytest]: https://pytest.org/
[tox]: https://tox.wiki/
